  "doc_id": "20470",
  "text": "Carbapenemase detection among carbapenem NSE is a major challenge in the routine laboratory. We designed screening strategies in order to retain 100% of carbapenemase-positive isolates while reaching the highest possible specificity by using the disc diffusion method. To reach our goal, we used data-driven cut-offs of diameter zones for commonly tested antibiotics including temocillin, and combined them to design an algorithm. Our strategies, which have been compared to those proposed by others using a similar approach [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , are shown to be highly relevant when sensitivity is the priority.",
